person.note:
John is Lucius Smith's second younger brother. Lucius refers to him throughout the journal, commonly 
in reference to labor shared by the brothers on family farm. John was particularly noted as helping 
Lucius with the labor on his well and his Mill. In the week of August 23rd 1862, Lucius also mentions 
that John was considering enlisting in the company that was presently raising, but expressed doubt
that he would actually commit. However, Lucius's prediction proved wrong within a year, as John and 
brother Newton both enlisted in June of 1863.

